Package JDBC

Class Msg

  • java.lang.Object
    • JDBC.Msg
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Msg
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Msg class represents a message object used for communication between the client and the server. It encapsulates various components of a database query, such as SELECT, FROM, WHERE, UPDATE, and INSERT INTO clauses, as well as additional data and metadata related to the message. The class provides methods for setting and retrieving different parts of the message, such as the message type, query components, data, file objects, and user information. It also includes utility methods for converting the data stored in the message to a list of objects of a specified type.
